  <reg:acttitle>Public Service Act</reg:acttitle>
  <reg:title>Excluded Employees Indemnity<in:br/> Protection Regulation</reg:title>
  <reg:content>
    <bcl:section id="d2e26" toc="false">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Definition</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>1</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>In this regulation, <in:term>excluded employee</in:term> means</bcl:text>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d2e40">
        <bcl:num>a</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>a person employed or appointed under the <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96385_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Public Service Act</in:doc></bcl:link> who is excluded from collective bargaining, and</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
      <bcl:paragraph id="d2e52">
        <bcl:num>b</bcl:num>
        <bcl:text>a former excluded employee within the meaning of paragraph (a).</bcl:text>
      </bcl:paragraph>
    </bcl:section>
    <bcl:section id="d2e62">
      <bcl:marginalnote>Indemnity protection</bcl:marginalnote>
      <bcl:num>2</bcl:num>
      <bcl:text>It is a term and condition of employment for excluded employees that the government provide indemnity protection, in accordance with the Excluded Employees (Legal Proceedings) Indemnity Regulation, in respect of conduct that occurs in the performance of employment within the meaning of that regulation.</bcl:text>
    </bcl:section>
    <reg:provisionsnote>[Provisions relevant to the enactment of this regulation: <bcl:link resource="leg" xlink:href="/legislation/96385_01" xlink:type="locator"><in:doc>Public Service Act</in:doc></bcl:link>, R.S.B.C. 1996, c. 385, section 25]</reg:provisionsnote>
  </reg:content>
</reg:regulation>